steps.description:
${echo}

Good observation. After doing this process MANY times with MANY different people, I find that clearing past feelings is almost always the better way to go.

However this is your body, your mind, and your life, and of course YOUR decision.

${echo}

Good. If the mixed feelings are very intense, like a shock or trauma from an accident or a very intense negative experience regarding or with ${s3}, then the [trauma relief](/tools/trauma-relief/NEW) process the place to start.

Otherwise, start with [resolving feelings](/tools/resolving-feelings/NEW).

Now as you think about both of these at the same time:

**The resource:**
${s17}

**And the cue:**
${s8}

Attend to the differences in how you see, hear, and experience them in your mind.

${echo}

Next notice what happens as you allow the cue image to become as bright (or as dim) as the resource image.

So you see both images in the same brightness/dimness.

${echo}

Now notice what happens as you allow the cue image to become as deep/flat as the resource image.

So you see both images in the same depth.

${echo}

Next notice what happens as you allow the cue image to become as vivid and focused as the resource image.

So you see both images in the same vividness & focus.

${echo}

Now hug, hold or kiss ${s3} in a certain way that feels pleasant you both.

So you can feel ${his2} touch on your skin and feel your touch on ${his2}’s.

${echo}

Now take a moment to experiment with different ways to further embellish the way you experience ${him2}.

Some people enjoy seeing their loved ones glow, and add sparkles and gloss to the experience. Some envision shining and radiating light.
